HEADWORD: Deadhead
<hw>Dead"head`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
receives free tickets for theaters, public conveyances, etc.</def>
<mark>[Colloq. U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A buoy. See under <er>Dead</er>,
<pos>a.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dead-hearted</ent>⟦br⟧
